    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-sausage-fried-brown-rice-with-sriracha-egg/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s] </strong>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Crumble your<strong> white cup mushrooms </strong>roughly</p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s] </strong>finely</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-sausage-fried-brown-rice-with-sriracha-egg/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Add your <strong>sausage meat</strong> (remove the paper if required!) to the pan and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-sausage-fried-brown-rice-with-sriracha-egg/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once beginning to brown, add the <strong>crumbled mushrooms</strong> and<strong> sliced pepper </strong>and cook for 4-5 min further or until softened and the sausage meat is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-sausage-fried-brown-rice-with-sriracha-egg/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add your<strong> red Thai curry paste </strong>and <strong>ginger & garlic paste </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-sausage-fried-brown-rice-with-sriracha-egg/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a medium, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-low heat</p><p>Once hot, crack your <strong>egg[s]</strong> into the pan</p><p>Cover with a lid and cook for 2-3 min or until done to your liking</p><p>Tip: Give your egg a little shake before you crack for a perfectly centred yolk!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-sausage-fried-brown-rice-with-sriracha-egg/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the egg is cooking, add the<strong> cooked brown rice </strong>to the pan with your <strong>soy sauce </strong>and give everything a good mix up until fully combined \u2013 this is your <strong>Thai-style sausage fried rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-sausage-fried-brown-rice-with-sriracha-egg/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> Thai-style fried brown rice </strong>in a bowl topped with the<strong> fried egg</strong></p><p>Drizzle over your <strong>sriracha </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and top with the<strong> sliced spring onion</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
